{"parentUuid":"bdec9a7d-c626-4958-86ed-982680e9aeed","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"C:\\src\\src-darren\\model-repo","sessionId":"ee315055-2095-46ab-ace9-670fade8c007","version":"2.1.23","gitBranch":"main","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Setup Gitea Remotes\n\nInitialize a git repository and configure it with three git remotes:\n- **origin**: External Gitea server (git.superpowerlabs.app)\n- **alt**: Local/pool Gitea server\n- **asgard**: Forgejo server (git.spl.tech)\n\n## Arguments\n\n- `` - (optional) Repository name. If not provided, uses current directory name.\n\n## Workflow\n\nExecute the following steps:\n\n### Step 1: Get repository name\n- Use provided argument, OR\n- Use current directory name as default (basename of PWD)\n- Display: \"Using repository name: {repo_name}\"\n\n### Step 2: Initialize Git and create first commit\n- Check if already a git repo (`git rev-parse --git-dir`)\n- If not, run `git init`\n- Ensure branch is `main` (`git branch -M main`)\n- Stage all files (`git add .`)\n- If there are staged changes OR no commits exist, create initial commit (`git commit -m \"Initial commit\"`)\n- Show current remotes (`git remote -v`)\n\n### Step 3: Configure remote repositories\n- **origin**: `ssh://git@git.superpowerlabs.app:2222/darren/{repo_name}.git`\n  - If origin exists, update URL with `git remote set-url`\n  - If not, add with `git remote add`\n- **alt**: `ssh://git@pool:2222/darren/{repo_name}.git`\n  - If alt exists, update URL with `git remote set-url`\n  - If not, add with `git remote add`\n- **asgard**: `ssh://git@git.spl.tech:2222/super-power-labs/{repo_name}.git`\n  - If asgard exists, update URL with `git remote set-url`\n  - If not, add with `git remote add`\n- Display configured remotes (`git remote -v`)\n\n### Step 4: SSH authentication setup\n- Check SSH key exists at `~/.ssh/id_ed25519`\n- If not found, error and tell user to generate one\n- Check if key is loaded in ssh-agent (`ssh-add -l`)\n- If not loaded, start ssh-agent if needed and add key\n\n### Step 5: Push to remote repositories\n- Push to origin with tracking: `git push -u origin main`\n- Push to alt with tracking: `git push -u alt main`\n- Push to asgard with tracking: `git push -u asgard main`\n- Note: Push-to-create works for personal repos; org repos on asgard may need to be created manually first\n\n### Step 6: Display summary\n```\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n✓ Repository setup complete!\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nRepository: {repo_name}\nBranch: main\nRemotes configured:\n  - origin: git.superpowerlabs.app\n  - alt: pool\n  - asgard: git.spl.tech\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n```bash\n# Use current directory name\n/zremotes\n\n# Specify custom repo name\n/zremotes my-custom-repo-name\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- SSH uses port 2222 for all remotes (Gitea/Forgejo servers)\n- Push-to-create auto-creates repos on push (enabled by default for personal repos)\n- SSH key must be set up and added to all git server accounts\n"}]},"isMeta":true,"uuid":"ce316c5c-95d0-4a6f-9bd6-26ade9311e1f","timestamp":"2026-01-29T20:38:20.291Z"}
